1
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:29,375
[HADAEBOU]
But for better, or for worse,

2
00:00:29,458 --> 00:00:32,333
Suruga- <i>sama</i> is
still Suruga- <i>sama</i> .

3
00:00:32,416 --> 00:00:34,458
Nothing will change that.

4
00:00:35,875 --> 00:00:37,500
[HACHIROU]
I understand.

5
00:00:37,583 --> 00:00:40,833
He would make
the perfect puppet.

6
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:42,791
And because that
cannot be allowed to happen,

7
00:00:42,875 --> 00:00:45,291
you have to rescue him
from Joujin's clutches.

8
00:00:45,375 --> 00:00:48,333
I assume that's why you're here.

9
00:00:48,416 --> 00:00:52,166
[JOUJIN] But if he cannot be
saved, he is to be slaughtered.

10
00:00:52,250 --> 00:00:54,625
That is precisely what
your master instructed you

11
00:00:54,708 --> 00:00:57,000
to do, if I'm not mistaken.

12
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:37,875
Bastard.

13
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,041
[HACHIROU growls]

14
00:02:44,916 --> 00:02:46,791
[yells]

15
00:02:55,041 --> 00:02:56,041
[JOUJIN grunts]

16
00:03:01,375 --> 00:03:02,666
[HACHIROU groans]

17
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,958
Have you forgotten?

18
00:03:06,041 --> 00:03:08,625
Your eye magic has
no effect on me.

19
00:03:08,708 --> 00:03:10,500
[HACHIROU growls]

20
00:03:11,916 --> 00:03:15,208
Your plan was clever,
attacking me by surprise,

21
00:03:15,291 --> 00:03:18,875
trying tso provoke a
sudden desire to harm you.

22
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:22,375
Heh. But not quite clever
enough, it would seem.

23
00:03:22,458 --> 00:03:24,166
[growls]

24
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:27,375
Feel free to try and
press your luck once more.

25
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:29,875
See if your technique
succeeds where it has failed

26
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:32,416
time and time again,
as I plunge my weapon

27
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,583
deeper into your chest.

28
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:41,125
[JOUJIN grunts]

29
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:46,166
I don't have to
rely on my eye magic.

30
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:48,333
I'll use this blade
to cut you down!

31
00:03:48,416 --> 00:03:49,958
Really?

32
00:03:50,041 --> 00:03:51,875
You think you can kill me?

33
00:03:51,958 --> 00:03:54,416
As simple as that?

34
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,041
[HACHIROU growls]

35
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:00,625
What's the matter, boy?

36
00:05:00,708 --> 00:05:03,125
Are you short of breath already?

37
00:05:03,208 --> 00:05:06,208
[pants]

38
00:05:23,625 --> 00:05:29,125
[rumbling]

39
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:36,708
[gasps]

40
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:38,500
[JOUJIN growls]

41
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,083
[groans]

42
00:05:49,083 --> 00:05:50,416
[HACHIROU grunts]

43
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:04,833
Shichigen, have you been hurt?

44
00:06:04,916 --> 00:06:07,000
You should worry
about Hachirou, not me.

45
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:08,791
We just crossed paths with him.

46
00:06:08,875 --> 00:06:10,500
[ALL gasp]

47
00:06:10,583 --> 00:06:12,125
We thought he might've
been making his way

48
00:06:12,208 --> 00:06:13,958
to meet up with you here.

49
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:16,791
Does he think he can
take down Murakumo by himself?

50
00:06:16,875 --> 00:06:18,583
Where did you last see Hachirou?

51
00:06:18,666 --> 00:06:20,375
Over by the eastern forest.

52
00:06:20,458 --> 00:06:22,333
We were trapped--
the Rain had riflemen

53
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:24,125
that were pinning us down.

54
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:25,125
Hachisu.

55
00:06:25,208 --> 00:06:26,916
Yes, leave it to me.

56
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,500
Shikibu, watch her.

57
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:30,666
Right. Shall we, Hibiki?

58
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:31,958
[HIBIKI growls]

59
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:35,291
[HACHIROU growls]

60
00:06:45,083 --> 00:06:46,541
[JOUJIN chuckles]

61
00:06:48,625 --> 00:06:50,916
[JOUJIN chuckles]

62
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:58,458
I know you'd
prepared for this mission.

63
00:06:58,541 --> 00:07:00,958
But are you sure it's going
to work out as planned?

64
00:07:01,041 --> 00:07:03,000
There's no way to be certain.

65
00:07:03,083 --> 00:07:05,833
The enemy might've predicted
we'd attempt a diversion,

66
00:07:05,916 --> 00:07:08,333
and thus, could have
prepared for us.

67
00:07:08,416 --> 00:07:10,833
[gasps]
Then why go through with it?

68
00:07:10,916 --> 00:07:14,041
New moves can
be revealed in a <i>damezumari</i> .

69
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:16,208
And what might that be?

70
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:18,208
A term from Go.

71
00:07:18,291 --> 00:07:20,166
When you and your opponent
are caught in the midst of

72
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:24,250
a chaotic battle,
unexpected moves may arise.

73
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:26,125
While our enemy
is focusing on the battle

74
00:07:26,208 --> 00:07:30,791
taking place right in front of
them, that's when you come in.

75
00:07:30,875 --> 00:07:34,333
Sure. But it
all sounds too risky.

76
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:36,375
I suspect they
should send us the signal

77
00:07:36,458 --> 00:07:38,166
any moment now.

78
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,833
Well, Saizou, what are
we supposed to do next?

79
00:07:43,916 --> 00:07:45,416
First, be quiet.

80
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,125
I'll have to think of something.

81
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:50,250
We'll try it once again.

82
00:08:07,083 --> 00:08:08,291
[gasps]

83
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:16,541
Suruga- <i>sama</i> .

84
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:22,375
Rui, you and Shichigen make sure
the boats are ready for us.

85
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:23,750
Are we retreating?

86
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:25,416
We have to secure our exit.

87
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:26,541
Now go on.

88
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:28,291
It's our duty.

89
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:30,000
I understand.

90
00:08:32,916 --> 00:08:34,916
I have a theory
I'd like to test.

91
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:38,041
If you please, I need to
observe you firing the cannon.

92
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:39,458
Why?

93
00:08:39,541 --> 00:08:42,041
What's the point in repeating
the exact same thing?

94
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:58,500
Come, sir.

95
00:08:58,583 --> 00:09:00,125
I'll help you escape.

96
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:02,041
I'll not leave here.

97
00:09:02,125 --> 00:09:03,666
Why stay, my lord?

98
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:06,666
Joujin is only using you to
further his own purposes.

99
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,000
When he's done with you,

100
00:09:08,083 --> 00:09:10,750
his only recourse will be
to put you to the sword!

101
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:12,416
[TADANAGA]
I'll not leave here.

102
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,958
I have different
orders if you refuse

103
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:15,166
to come back with me.

104
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:16,750
Suruga- <i>sama</i> , I beg you.

105
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:18,708
His Excellency, High Priest
Tenkai, has told me

106
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:21,083
to take your life,
should you remain.

107
00:09:21,166 --> 00:09:22,208
Are you certain you'll not take

108
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:24,291
this chance to go?

109
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:28,375
I'll not leave here.
I'll not leave here.

110
00:09:28,458 --> 00:09:30,375
I'll not leave here.

111
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:32,416
[gasps]
I see now.

112
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,208
This one must be
some kind of fake.

113
00:09:34,291 --> 00:09:35,208
Damn it!

114
00:09:35,291 --> 00:09:38,041
[NEIRICHIOU chuckles]

115
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:04,583
[SAIZOU grunts]

116
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:06,583
[KUJAKU gasps]

117
00:10:09,541 --> 00:10:11,333
[KUJAKU growls]

118
00:10:11,416 --> 00:10:12,708
[gasps]

119
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:19,125
Now you've heard it
for yourself, Lord Tadanaga,

120
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:22,083
and it seems to be even
worse than we first expected.

121
00:10:22,166 --> 00:10:24,458
I'm afraid the inhabitants of
Chiyoda Castle have played

122
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:27,708
their hand, and shown they have
every intention of killing you.

123
00:10:27,791 --> 00:10:31,916
[growls] You've shown
your true colors at last!

124
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,041
How dare you plot against me!

125
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:36,500
Crawl back to
your master, vile serpent!

126
00:10:36,583 --> 00:10:40,625
And tell him that with Joujin's
help, I'll rule all of Japan!

127
00:10:40,708 --> 00:10:42,250
Suruga- <i>sama</i> .

128
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:52,375
Ahh. Even if
it was a mere illusion,

129
00:10:52,458 --> 00:10:55,750
he still slew it without
a moment's hesitation.

130
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:58,916
Suruga- <i>sama</i> , ruling
can be a cruel thing,

131
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,250
with great peril on
the heels of power.

132
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:02,500
[HADAEBOU growls]

133
00:11:16,666 --> 00:11:18,625
[NEIRICHIOU chuckles]

134
00:11:31,041 --> 00:11:32,375
Go.

135
00:11:32,458 --> 00:11:35,500
Return to them, and tell them
what you've witnessed.

136
00:11:35,583 --> 00:11:39,291
Tell them how terrifying we
Joujinshuu are.

137
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:50,041
[JOUJIN] You can die here,
or you can join me.

138
00:11:50,125 --> 00:11:51,416
[HACHIROU]
Join you?

139
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:53,458
What the devil are you planning?

140
00:11:54,875 --> 00:11:57,208
[JOUJIN] We no longer have
any cause to defeat the leader

141
00:11:57,291 --> 00:11:59,333
of the Five Treasures of Kouga.

142
00:11:59,416 --> 00:12:02,875
Our goal has long
since been achieved.

143
00:12:02,958 --> 00:12:05,125
So instead, you try
to convince me to join you?

144
00:12:05,208 --> 00:12:07,833
Betrayal is the
way of the world, my boy.

145
00:12:07,916 --> 00:12:10,041
You wouldn't be the first ninja
to change allegiances

146
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:11,541
when it suited him.

147
00:12:11,625 --> 00:12:14,041
Don't let hatred and the
desire for revenge blind you

148
00:12:14,125 --> 00:12:16,125
to what's being offered!

149
00:12:16,208 --> 00:12:18,541
[HACHIROU] My loyalty
is not so easily traded.

150
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:20,041
Tell me what you want!

151
00:12:20,125 --> 00:12:24,458
You, Hachirou, or rather,
the pedigree you both possess.

152
00:12:24,541 --> 00:12:26,291
We want the blood
flowing through the veins

153
00:12:26,375 --> 00:12:30,458
of the last scions of the
Kouga and Iga ninja clans!

154
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:33,000
To put it plainly,
you would use me to your ends--

155
00:12:33,083 --> 00:12:36,583
use us all, as if we were
nothing more than beasts!

156
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:39,208
[JOUJIN] The only other choice
that remains is to die here,

157
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:41,166
now, by my hand.

158
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:43,291
[HACHIROU]
You underestimate me, monster!

159
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:45,083
[JOUJIN]
Monster, am I?

160
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:47,875
Surely the same should
apply to the two of you.

161
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:51,000
Between you, you have the powers
of both monsters and demons,

162
00:12:51,083 --> 00:12:53,125
to set the world itself alight!

163
00:12:53,208 --> 00:12:55,000
[HACHIROU]
I've heard enough.

164
00:12:55,083 --> 00:12:58,375
This will be the last
time I make this offer.

165
00:12:58,458 --> 00:13:00,541
Will you join me, or die?

166
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:03,291
I refuse!

167
00:13:03,375 --> 00:13:05,958
You prideful fool!

168
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:07,125
[HIBIKI]
Hachirou!

169
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:09,416
[JOUJIN]
Hmm?

170
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,041
Hibiki!

171
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:15,041
[SHIKIBU growls, yells]

172
00:13:15,125 --> 00:13:16,625
[JOUJIN growls]

173
00:13:16,708 --> 00:13:17,708
[groans]

174
00:13:35,375 --> 00:13:38,750
[JOUJIN]
Kujaku. Can you hear me?

175
00:13:40,125 --> 00:13:41,541
Joujin- <i>sama</i> ?

176
00:13:41,625 --> 00:13:44,666
[JOUJIN] Fire the Shiroku cannon
towards the eastern hill.

177
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:46,791
We'll flush those pests out.

178
00:13:46,875 --> 00:13:49,500
The Shiroku cannon?
Are you certain?

179
00:13:49,583 --> 00:13:52,166
Won't the force of
the blasts kill them?

180
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:54,083
If it does,
they were never of any value

181
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:56,166
to us in the first place.

182
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:57,541
Very well.

183
00:13:59,083 --> 00:14:01,000
[bell rings]

184
00:14:09,041 --> 00:14:11,125
They're shifting
the cannon's direction!

185
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:12,791
It's turning east.

186
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,125
[SHIKIBU]
It's pointing right at us!

187
00:14:16,208 --> 00:14:17,666
Run along with
the banks of the river,

188
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:19,791
or else you might get
caught up in a landslide!

189
00:14:19,875 --> 00:14:22,166
[bell rings]

190
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:42,500
[SHIKIBU groans]

191
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:43,958
Shikibu!

192
00:15:13,583 --> 00:15:15,166
That pillar of light.

193
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:16,750
Is it the Ouka?

194
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:17,750
[SAIZOU gasps]

195
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,000
Well.

196
00:15:33,458 --> 00:15:35,958
It's grown even stronger.

197
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:37,458
Gorone?

198
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:39,375
[gasps]

199
00:15:39,458 --> 00:15:40,708
Could it be?

200
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:44,333
[RUI]
Shichigen, is that...?

201
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:45,708
It's the Ouka.

202
00:16:09,208 --> 00:16:14,500
[BOTH pant]

203
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:18,458
[JOUJIN]
Splendid!

204
00:16:18,541 --> 00:16:20,875
I will ask you, once more.

205
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:24,625
Will you entrust your
great power unto me?

206
00:16:24,708 --> 00:16:27,375
Join us, and we
can take over the world.

207
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:36,250
[JOUJIN]
Stop it, children.

208
00:16:36,333 --> 00:16:39,000
You have yet to
master this technique.

209
00:16:39,083 --> 00:16:41,125
Without control
there's only danger.

210
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:44,125
Using it again
could kill you both.

211
00:16:44,208 --> 00:16:46,583
[HACHIROU snarls]

212
00:16:46,666 --> 00:16:49,000
[SHIKIBU groans]

213
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:58,208
Ugh. So you would choose
to sacrifice your own lives

214
00:16:58,291 --> 00:17:00,125
rather than join me?

215
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:05,666
Magoroku!

216
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:14,333
[JOUJIN groans]

217
00:17:14,416 --> 00:17:15,833
[MAGOROKU]
Joujin- <i>sama</i> !

218
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,250
My, how splendid!

219
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:35,500
I'm beginning to understand
Joujin- <i>sama</i> 's obsession

220
00:17:35,583 --> 00:17:37,333
with those ninja brats!

221
00:17:55,958 --> 00:17:58,291
[SHIKIBU groans]

222
00:18:02,541 --> 00:18:03,500
[SHIKIBU]
Hachirou!

223
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:04,750
Hibiki!

224
00:18:08,916 --> 00:18:10,541
[SAIZOU]
I'm counting on you, Utsutsu.

225
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:11,666
[UTSUTSU]
Right!

226
00:18:17,041 --> 00:18:18,416
So disappointing.

227
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:21,083
Of course, they have
no choice but to give up now.

228
00:18:48,125 --> 00:18:49,958
Joujin- <i>sama</i> !

229
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:53,875
I am unscathed,
no need for you to worry.

230
00:18:53,958 --> 00:18:55,833
Those children,
this is the second time

231
00:18:55,916 --> 00:18:57,250
they've used the Ouka.

232
00:18:57,333 --> 00:19:00,583
But it would appear they
haven't fully mastered it yet.

233
00:19:00,666 --> 00:19:03,416
I trust that
they will, given time.

234
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:07,458
We'll take them later, when
they've let down their guard.

235
00:19:07,541 --> 00:19:10,583
As you commanded us,
we sent Tenkai's servant,

236
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:13,333
the monk Hadaebou,
back to his master alive.

237
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:15,416
Excellent work.

238
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,625
Tenkai will be quite
flustered when he learns

239
00:19:17,708 --> 00:19:19,708
of what has transpired.

240
00:19:19,791 --> 00:19:21,583
[TADANAGA]
Joujin!

241
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:23,750
If Hadaebou was allowed
to leave here alive,

242
00:19:23,833 --> 00:19:26,541
that may as well have
been a declaration of war!

243
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:28,958
I say we cross the river and
attack while we still have

244
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:30,875
the element of surprise!

245
00:19:30,958 --> 00:19:34,208
[JOUJIN] There's no need for
such hastiness, my lord!

246
00:19:34,291 --> 00:19:37,250
Strategy is an important
part of warfare.

247
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:39,375
Our first course of action
should be to cause our foe

248
00:19:39,458 --> 00:19:42,250
to panic, and thus
make mistakes.

249
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:43,375
Yes...

250
00:19:43,458 --> 00:19:46,000
I suppose you're
right about that.

251
00:19:46,083 --> 00:19:48,791
What's become of Kujaku?

252
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:50,291
Last I checked,
he was out playing

253
00:19:50,375 --> 00:19:52,125
on top of the cannon.

254
00:19:52,208 --> 00:19:54,250
Ha! Even after all these years,

255
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:57,166
he still somehow maintains
the heart of a child.

256
00:20:04,583 --> 00:20:06,500
[SAIZOU]
If this fails, it's all over.

257
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:08,916
We only have
one cannonball left.

258
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,291
